{[%evp 0,44,34,26,71,71,71,56,61,61,56,32,26,33,75,30,43,12,12,-12,-12,-8,-8,-11,3,-25,-4,-4,22,22,38,50,45,-26,-38,-11,-35,-12,-5,-33,-8,1,11,9,1,13,36]} 1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 Bf5 4. Nf3 e6 5. Be2 Nd7 6. O-O a5 7. a4 f6 8. c4 {The most popular and principled move. After Black has weakened his kingside light squares despite being completely undeveloped in this area of the board, it makes sense for White to open the position in the centre.} fxe5 9. dxe5 (9. cxd5 {Taking on d5 immediately seems to slightly favour Black, who gets rid of his weakness on e6 and is now less vulnerable to Nd4 ideas.} exd5 10. dxe5 (10. Nxe5 Bb4 11. Nd3 (11. Bd3 Qf6 12. Bd2 Ne7 13. Bxb4 axb4 14. Nd2 Nxe5 15. dxe5 Qh6 16. Bxf5 Nxf5 17. Nf3 O-O $132) (11. Bd2 Ne7 $132) 11... Bd6 12. Bf4 Ndf6 13. Nd2 Ne7 14. Bxd6 Qxd6 15. Qb3 O-O $132) 10... Bc5 {Again it's clear that Black benefits more than White from the inclusion of a7-a5 and a2-a4. Control over the dark squares is vital for Black's stability and counterplay, and Black has full control over the b4-square.} 11. Nbd2 (11. Nd4 Ne7 12. Nc3 $2 {This mistake, made by a very strong grandmaster, is a good indicator of how difficult and dangerous this line is for White.} (12. g4 Bxb1 13. Rxb1 Nxe5 $1 14. Ne6 Qd6 15. Nxc5 (15. Nxg7+ $2 Kd7 $17) 15... Qxc5 16. b4 $5 axb4 17. Bd2 Qd6 18. Rxb4 O-O $132) 12... Nxe5 13. Bh5+ N5g6 14. Be3 (14. g4 Bd7) 14... Bb4 15. Bg5 O-O 16. Bxg6 hxg6 $17 {0-1 Ter Sahakyan,S (2625)-Shams,M (2167) Yerevan op-A 4th 2022 (1)}) 11... Ne7 12. Nb3 Bb6 13. Nbd4 O-O 14. Nh4 Nc5 $1 15. Be3 Qc7 (15... Bd7 16. Bg4) 16. Rc1 Bd7 $132) 9... Bc5 10. Nbd2 (10. cxd5 exd5 {transposes.}) (10. Nd4 Ne7 11. Nc3 $6 (11. cxd5 $142 Bxd4 $5 12. Qxd4 cxd5 13. f4 O-O 14. Nc3 Nc6 $132) 11... Nxe5 $1 {White has no sufficient compensation for the pawn. Black's centre is very strong and White's initiative is only temporary.} (11... Qb6 $2 12. Nxf5 Nxf5 13. cxd5 cxd5 {1/ 2-1/2 Darini,P (2426)-Ashraf,A (2285) Rasht 2022 (9)} 14. Bb5 $1 O-O-O 15. Bf4 Rhf8 16. Nxd5 $5 exd5 17. Rc1 $40) 12. Be3 (12. g4 $6 dxc4 $1 13. Be3 Bxd4 14. Qxd4 Qxd4 15. Bxd4 Nxg4 $19) 12... Qd6 $17) 10... Ne7 11. Nb3 Ba7 $5 {This somewhat counter-intuitive knight retreat is very important in this position.} ({After} 11... Bb6 $6 12. Nfd4 $1 (12. Nbd4 $6 O-O 13. Be3 Bxd4 14. Nxd4 Nxe5 15. g4 c5 $1 16. Nxf5 exf5 17. Bxc5 fxg4 18. cxd5 Nf3+ 19. Bxf3 gxf3 $11 {1/ 2-1/2 Ter Sahakyan,S (2531)-Donchenko,A (2597) Wch Rapid Almaty 2022 (7)}) 12... Nxe5 13. c5 $1 $16 {, White wins an important tempo. Next move will be g2-g4, and Black has no defence.}) 12. Bg5 $5 {Trying to provoke h7-h6, although it's not clear whether the weaknesses created on the kingside are more important than the benefits for Black: The retreat square h7 and control of g5.} (12. Bd2 O-O $5 {This temporary pawn sacrifice is similar to the mainline.} (12... Bb8 $5 {is a good alternative.} 13. cxd5 (13. Bc3 O-O 14. Nbd4 Nc5 15. Rc1 (15. Nxf5 Nxf5 16. cxd5 exd5 $13) 15... Ba7 16. b4 Ne4 17. bxa5 Bg4 $13) (13. Nbd4 Nxe5 14. cxd5 exd5 15. Nxe5 Bxe5 16. Bh5+ Bg6 17. Bg5 Bxh5 18. Qxh5+ g6 19. Qh3 Qd7 $132) 13... exd5 14. Bc3 (14. Nfd4 Nxe5 15. f4 N5g6 $132) 14... O-O 15. Bd3 Bg4 $5 16. Bxh7+ Kh8 17. Bc2 Bxf3 18. gxf3 Ng6 $44) 13. Bxa5 Qe8 14. Bc7 (14. Bb4 c5) 14... Bb8 15. Bxb8 Qxb8 16. a5 Ng6 17. cxd5 (17. Nfd4 Qxe5 $132) 17... exd5 $132) (12. Nfd4 {Now Black must not fear the following complications:} Nxe5 $1 {Again, thanks to the bishop on a7, there is no tempo-winning c4-c5 and g2-g4.} 13. g4 Be4 (13... dxc4 $5 14. gxf5 cxb3 15. Nxe6 Qxd1 16. Bxd1 Kd7 17. Bxb3 Nf3+ 18. Kh1 Nxf5 $11) 14. Nxe6 Qd6 15. Nxg7+ Kd7 16. Bf4 Nf3+ 17. Bxf3 Qxf4 18. Bxe4 Qxe4 19. Re1 Qxc4 20. Ne6 Qb4 21. Rc1 Rae8 $132) (12. cxd5 exd5 13. Nbd4 O-O 14. Nh4 $1 (14. Be3 Qb8 $5 15. Bg5 Bc5 $132) 14... Nc5 $1 {Black is unable to keep the important light-squared bishop, but he will be able to block the e-pawn with a knight.} 15. Be3 Bd7 16. Bg4 Qc8 $5 17. Bxd7 Qxd7 18. Rc1 Ne4 19. f3 Nc5 (19... g5 $5 20. fxe4 gxh4 21. e6 Rxf1+ 22. Qxf1 Qe8 $132) 20. Kh1 Ne6 21. Nxe6 Qxe6 22. Bxa7 Rxa7 23. f4 Raa8 24. Qb3 Rab8 $132) 12... h6 13. Bd2 O-O $1 (13... Bb8 $6 {With the pawn on h6, this is no longer a viable option:} 14. cxd5 exd5 $2 15. Nfd4 Nxe5 16. f4 N5g6 17. Nxf5 Nxf5 18. Bh5 $18) 14. Bxa5 Qe8 15. Bc7 Bb8 $1 16. Bxb8 (16. Bd6 Bxd6 17. exd6 Ng6 18. Nbd4 Be4 19. Nd2 Nf4 20. Nxe4 dxe4 $132) 16... Qxb8 {Black will regain the material balance and equalise.} 17. a5 (17. cxd5 exd5 18. Qd2 Nxe5 19. Nxe5 Qxe5 $11) (17. Re1 Ng6 18. Nbd4 Ndxe5 19. Nxe5 Nxe5 $132) 17... Ng6 18. Nfd4 Qxe5 19. Nxf5 Qxf5 20. Bg4 Qf7 21. cxd5 exd5 22. Nd4 Rae8 $132 *

